						               													<description>Three games in one packaged in a wooden box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. The Smiley Face Game &amp;#10;Players roll dice and race through a 9x9 square grid collecting smiley face disks. The disks are placed at random with the exception of the triple smiley face which is placed at the last space (no. 81). Landing on a space occupied by another player pushes a piece back to the next available unoccupied space. Players collect smiley face disks if they land on a space occupied by a disk. If a smiley face is passed by all players, that disk is placed on the highest available number on the board. Landing on a smiley face disk gives another turn; landing on a double smiley face gives two extra turns. The game ends when a player lands with an exact roll on the last space (no. 81). The player with the most smiley faces at the end wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. The Smiley Face Game with no dice&amp;#10;Setup is the same as the first game. Players do not move according to dice rolls but according to a chosen number between 1-5.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Odd Even Tag&amp;#10;The game board is a hexagonal ring formed by smaller hexagons. Players choose to play as even or odd. Player take turns rolling dice and the player counters are moved according to the number of dice rolled and if it's odd or even.  The first player to tag the other wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
